01556205,0.14209615,0.03516543,0.03920217,0.04101700,-0.02587763,-0.01895209,0.02564687,0.09424666,0.03919125,0.00765771,0.07653320,-0.02663098,0.03070553,0.00005679,0.02792407,0.01980679,-0.05657782,0.00411679,-0.05021632,0.06250856,0.00547803,0.07024934,0.06032814,-0.04021787,-0.00013943,-0.08769991,-0.02643868,-0.04937271,0.00710961,-0.01444842,0.01555717,0.04258294,0.03216927,0.00220361,0.06583522,0.01073133,-0.05160622,-0.01643902,0.00970545,-0.04440496,0.01750704,-0.01546769,-0.00275675]',E'Using Helm\n\nAlternatively, you may use [Helm](https://helm.sh/docs/intro/quickstart/); which is a package manager for Kubernetes.\n\nInstall the Helm repository:\n\n```sh\n$> helm repo add mysql-operator https://mysql.github.io/mysql-operator/\n$> helm repo update\n```\n\nThen deploy the operator using the just added repository:\n\n```sh\n$> helm install mysql-operator mysql-operator/mysql-operator --namespace mysql-operator --create-namespace\n```','{"source": "mysql", "version": "9.0", "language": "sql", "title": "MySQL Operator for Kubernetes", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/mysql/mysql-operator/blob/trunk/README.md", "topics": "mysql/operator,README", "categories": "database,sql,relational,kubernetes,operator"}');
