0.12529483,-0.00925926,-0.01648591,0.07182916,-0.07957526,0.00794832,-0.02592653,0.09622144,-0.00883878,-0.02894892,0.06873390,-0.00073464,0.04613003,0.01199931,0.04681892,-0.03274859,0.02886674,-0.00451785,-0.01788612,0.06264208,-0.01691932,0.04910303,0.01669916,0.03283879,-0.08435173,-0.08472945,0.02820960,-0.02761929,0.00628771,-0.04323751,0.02000452,0.00220504,0.04858755,0.06042697,0.01787122,-0.01621504,-0.03270098,-0.00853543,-0.00952900,-0.02047714,0.00584209,0.00413733,0.03646041]',E'Connecting to MySQL InnoDB Cluster\n\nA MySQL InnoDB Cluster `Service` is created inside the Kubernetes cluster:\n\n```sh\n$> kubectl get service mycluster\n\nNAME        TYPE        CLUSTER-IP      EXTERNAL-IP   PORT(S)                                                           AGE\nmycluster   ClusterIP   10.110.228.51   <none>        3306/TCP,33060/TCP,6446/TCP,6448/TCP,6447/TCP,6449/TCP,6450/TCP   26h\n```\n\nThe ports represent read-write and read-only ports for the MySQL Protocol and the X Protocol. \nUse `describe` or see the documentation for additional information.','{"source": "mysql", "version": "9.0", "language": "sql", "title": "MySQL Operator for Kubernetes", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/mysql/mysql-operator/blob/trunk/README.md", "topics": "mysql/operator,README", "categories": "database,sql,relational,kubernetes,operator"}');
